page.title: 01HOUSING
page.content: Squares 11 and 12 are almost equally divided between open space and housing. A great variety of different types and quality of housing is found in these squares.There is a small part of a large coucil estate in square 12.Quite close by are large detached and semi-detached houses and another zone of smaller semi-detached houses.In square 11 the houses are very different being partly modern - inter-war semi-detached and partly older 3 storey Edwardian houses arranged in pairs and fours.There is also a small area of older terraced housing,possibly late Victorian.
